<task id="046" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Frontend — Wire modal launch (Path A): "Open in Compose" command-bar via launch-resolver</title>
    <phase>Phase 4: Frontend — SpaarkeAi Compose Surface</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <tags>frontend, react, typescript, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Task tags include 'fluent-ui' (UI implementation per ADR-021)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Wraps `ComposeWorkspace` (Task 042); serialized.</parallel-reason>
    <dependencies>042</dependencies>
    <blocks>060</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the Path A entry point: a command-bar "Open in Compose" button on the `sprk_document` model-driven form that opens the SpaarkeAi modal shell with `ComposeWorkspace` mounted, full-screen toggle enabled (reusing the existing modal pattern from ConversationPane / launch-resolver). The modal passes the `sprk_documentid` + drive-item id as context so `ComposeEditor` (Task 045) loads the DOCX.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React/TypeScript developer fluent in the SpaarkeAi `launch-resolver` pattern, command-bar ribbon integration (Power Apps model-driven), and the existing modal shell with full-screen toggle.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Clicking "Open in Compose" on a `sprk_document` record opens the SpaarkeAi modal with `ComposeWorkspace` mounted, full-screen toggle works, and the document context (id + drive-item id) reaches `ComposeEditor`. Build green; ui-test green; dark mode renders.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-19 mandates the Path A entry: command-bar "Open in Compose" → modal shell with full-screen toggle. The decision is locked in CLAUDE.md ("Path A entry UX: Modal with full-screen toggle — reuses existing SpaarkeAi pattern"). The existing `launch-resolver.ts` is the canonical pattern (ConversationPane uses it). This task adds a new resolver entry for the `compose-editor` target plus the ribbon button definition.
    </background>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Modal + full-screen toggle use Fluent UI v9 dark mode via semantic tokens.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Auth context passed through `@spaarke/auth` only; no manual token handling at the launch boundary.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">REUSE existing modal pattern + `launch-resolver` (ConversationPane reference); NO new modal abstraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No custom DOCX-feature integration outside TipTap OOB — the launch path forwards only the document id + drive-item id, not feature flags.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <justification>
    <existing>`src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts` already routes Conversation + other modal targets. The modal shell + full-screen toggle exist.</existing>
    <extension>Yes — this task EXTENDS `launch-resolver.ts` with a `compose-editor` target entry and adds a ribbon button definition. No new abstraction is created.</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>FR-19 fails — Path A has no entry point; users cannot reach Compose from a `sprk_document` record; the smoke test (Phase 6) has no UI button to fire.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/plan.md</file>
